<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Berasategui Sets Up Barcelona Final Clash With Martin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Spaniard Alberto Berasategui saved
four set points to set up a final tie against American Todd Martin
in the Barcelona Open on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Berasategui, seeded seventh, beat his compatriot Carlos Moya
7-6 (11-9), 6-4, while Martin defeated Italy's Andrea Gaudenzi
6-4, 7-6 (7-5) in the other semifinal.
</P>
<P>
Berasategui, who routed Moya 6-1, 6-1 on his way to win last
week's Estoril tournament, came back from 6-3 down in the
tie-break to win the first set before he went 4-1 down in the
second.
</P>
<P>
But Berasategui won five games in a row, holding off Moya's
third consecutive asking for the title of the event.
</P>
<P>
Martin became the first American to reach the final since Eddie
Dibbs in 1979 after his Italian opponet double faulted out on
match point and gave the match to Martin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
