<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Road Accidents Kill 11 People in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Eleven people were killed and 202
injured, including 47 seriously, in road accidents throughout
Greece as of Thursday.
</P>
<P>
There were a total of 144 road accidents in Greece since
Thursday afternoon when thousands of Greeks left cities for their
Easter vacations, according to the semi-official Athens News
Agency (ANA).
</P>
<P>
Greece has one of the worst records in Europe for the number of
road accidents which kill some 2,500 people and injury 30,000 each
year.
</P>
<P>
Since September last year, Greece has taken strict measures,
including the use of breathylyser tests for drivers, to reduce the
number of road accidents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
