<DOCNO> XIE19980419.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-18 17:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2.4 Million Tourists Visit Syria in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Syrian Minister of Tourism
Danhow Daoud said Saturday that 2.4 million Arab and foreign
tourists visited Syria in 1997, compared with 1.4 million in 1990.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony of the First Spring Festival in Hamah,
some 220 kilometers north of Syrian capital Damascus, Daoud said
the increase of foreign tourists was the result of a number of
measure adopted by the government to encourage foreign investment
in the tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
The measures include tax and duty exemptions, and allowing
investors in the tourism sector to import construction materials,
vehicles and equipment necessary for their projects, Daoud said.
</P>
</TEXT>
