<HEADLINE> Somalia: Tension Mounts As Pressure for Hostage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Tension has mounted up along
the former green line dividing the capital Mogadishu as
militiamen are seen being positioned there Saturday morning, the
first since late January this year.
</P>
<P>
A number of armed militiamen have been deployed by the faction
led by Ali Mahdi Mohamed along every section of the cross line
leading to south Mogadishu, a line which has been dismantled
after the Cairo agreement was endorsed by factional leaders early
this year.
</P>
<P>
According to sources close to the militia officials along the
green line, the deployment has something to do with the
continuous abductions of 10 International Commission of Red Cross
(ICRC) staff members in north Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
It is suspected that the militiamen holding the ICRC members
might try to cross the line into southern Mogadishu if the
pressure on them further increases, the militia sources said.
</P>
<P>
However, serious negotiations are going on for the fourth day
Saturday between representatives from the abductors and those of
the Abgal clan led by its leader Imam Mohamud Imam Omar, and
other religious leaders, who are trying to secure the release of
the Red Cross aid workers.
</P>
<P>
It was thought that it wouldn't take Ali Mahdi more than 24
hours to secure the release of the hostages, but now it seems
that it will take much longer.
</P>
<P>
Ali Mahdi and his close associates are working hard to secure
the release, but the abductors are still stucking to their
demands of having huge ransom exceeding nine million U.S. Dollars
paid to them before the release, according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
Other sources said the abduction has also got something to do
with politics.
</P>
<P>
They said that elements opposing Ali Mahdi are playing a
political card by holding the hostages so as to prove that Ali
Mahdi's position is weak.
</P>
<P>
A bus driver dropped his passengers at the green line, saying
passengers are afraid that armed gangs has started looting.
</P>
</TEXT>
