<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Currency Falls to New Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian currency has
weakened to nearly seven Birr against one U.S. Dollar, the lowest
since it was devalued in October, 1992.
</P>
<P>
The National Bank of Ethiopia announced Saturday that the
official exchange rate will be 6.997 Birr to one U.S. Dollar from
April 20 to April 26, compared to 6.88 Birr last week.
</P>
<P>
On the foreign exchange auction held Saturday, the highest bid
rate was 7.115 Birr whereas the lowest was 6.921 for one U.S.
Dollar, said the bank.
</P>
<P>
It added that the total foreign exchange available at the
auction amounted to 17 million U.S. Dollars and the bidders who
offered rates of 6.997 and above for one U.S. Dollar won the full
amount they tendered for.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia launched the foreign exchange auction system in May,
1993. The auction is held weekly at the National Bank of
Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Commercial Bank of Ethiopia announced Saturday
that the buying price for one U.S. Dollar is 6.95 Birr while the
selling price is 7.1469 Birr for one U.S. Dollar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
