<HEADLINE> ECOSOC's Vice President Comments on its Special </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The discussion on the
global financial integration and development have demonstrated
that international institutions and national governments still
have a lot to learn about responding to the forces of global
financial integration, the Vice-President of the UN Economic and
Social Council Francesco Paolo Fulci said here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the ending session of the high-level discussion
held this morning, Fulci said all the participants have reached
the common view: there is a need to strengthen the global
architecture; prevention is better than cure; actions are required
at both the international and national levels.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president said from a technical point of view, there
seems to be universal agreement that more information, greater
transparency and improved monitoring are indispensable in reducing
the possibility of financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
He said the reason, version, motivation and inspiration behind
the free discussion all focus on a single goal: to make the world
a better place in which to live for all the people of the planet,
by giving the developing countries, especially the least developed
countries, a better chance to improve their sort. 
</P>
</TEXT>
