<HEADLINE> 86 Kilograms of Heroin Seized in Eastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Turkish police seized a total of
86 kilograms of heroin Saturday in a raid in Baskale town in
eastern Van province, according to the semi-official Anatolia News
Agency.
</P>
<P>
Police stormed a civilian house in the town of Guroluk village
and seized the haul. Ten suspects were arrested on the spot.
</P>
<P>
The drugs came from Iran and were destined for the European
black market, a police spokesman said on condition of anonymity.
</P>
<P>
International drug dealers often use Turkey as a main route to
traffick narcotics from west and southeast Asia to Europe. 
</P>
