<HEADLINE> Shenyang Haishi Stuns Vanguard Huandao 2-1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Shenyang Haishi shocked its
star-studded opponents Vanguard Huandao with a 2-1 victory in the
sixth round of the Chinese soccer league on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Haishi, savoring its first sweet victory of the season, surged
ahead with two goals netted in the first half through its Korean
import Se Min Chol in the eighth minute and Qu Nannan in the 23rd
minute with a precise header.
</P>
<P>
Huandao, that boasted of several members of the national squad,
failed to convert any opportunity into goal until the 67th minute
when substitute Xu Xin found the target eventually.
</P>
<P>
In other games, Shandong Luneng also anchored its first win of
2-0 over Shenzhen Pingan on its home turf, which forced Pingan to
settle for its fourth consecutive loss.
</P>
<P>
Deng Lejun, who inked a record transfer of 2.01 million RMB
from Beijing Guo'an to Luneng, scored in the 36th and 58th minutes
through a header and a penalty pick.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Dalian Wanda extended its lead by trouncing
visiting Qingdao Hainiu 4-0 with ease, retaining its top spot in
the overall standings with 16 points.
</P>
<P>
Hainiu's head coach Li Yingfa, a native from Dalian, said that
Wanda remained as the favorites to clinch the league title as
seldom a Chinese club could hold back its powerful attacks.
</P>
</TEXT>
