<HEADLINE> Todd Martin Wins Conde de Godo Clay-court Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Unseeded American Todd Martin
upset seventh-seeded Spaniard Alberto Berasategui in four sets
Sunday to win the 950,000 dollars Conde de Godo ATP Tour clay
court event in Barcelona.
</P>
<P>
Martin, ranked 65th in the world, downed Berasategui 6-2, 1-6,
6-3, 6-2 to become the first American to win the event.
</P>
<P>
The final lasted two hours with Martin in control against an
opponent who was aiming for his second straight title after he won
the Estoril tournament in Portugal last week.
</P>
<P>
It was Martin's first ATP Tour victory since he triumphed in
Sydney, Australia, in January 1996. He has been plagued by
injuries since that time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
