<HEADLINE> Li Fang Beaten in Makarska Tennis Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Li Fang of China was
toppled by a Czech qualifier in the final of the Makarska tennis
open on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Kvetoslava Hrdlickova of the Czech Republic upset Li Fang 6-3,
6-1 to win her first WTA tournament.
</P>
<P>
"I think I played so well today and that she had no chance.
It's my first WTA tournament title and I'm happy it happened in
Makarska," said Hrdlickova.
</P>
<P>
Hrdlickova, ranked 140th, outpowered Li Fang with fierce and
precise shots that she maintained throughout, by breaking serve
twice in the first set and even surging to a 5-0 lead in the
second.
</P>
<P>
Li Fang, who ranked 49th, failed to stage any serious challenge
and even failed to convert a single breakpoint out of seven
opportunities.
</P>
<P>
The win pushed Hrdlickova into the Top 100 for the first time
in her career. 
</P>
