wounded Sunday in a violent clash near the West Bank city Hebron
due to a land dispute, Israeli Army said.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by Israeli Army Spokesman's Office said a
group of Palestinians ambushed several settlers in the hills in
Maom near Hebron. One of the Palestinians took over a gun from
the settlers and opened fire at them.
</P>
<P>
One settler was shot dead and another wounded in the shooting,
the statement added. The wounded was evacuated to hospital by a
military helicopter. (Israel-Palestine-Shooting) 
