<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier on Taiwan Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Qian Qichen has
recently emphasized the principles of peaceful reunification and
"one country, two systems" in solving the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
"We place our hopes in Taiwanese compatriots in the improvement
of the cross-straits relations and in the peaceful reunification
of the motherland," Qian said during a visit to Shanghai city and
Jiangsu province on April 12-19.
</P>
<P>
He added that the campaign against separatism and "Taiwan
independence" has had some results, and that international feeling
is in favor of the inland area of China.
</P>
<P>
He asked government departments to keep the interests of
Taiwanese in mind when handling Taiwan-related matters, and to
increase contacts with Taiwan compatriots to reach a common
understanding.
</P>
<P>
Qian affirmed the contribution made by Taiwanese businesspeople
to economic cooperation between Taiwan and the mainland, pointing
to its huge market potential and many business opportunities.
</P>
<P>
The rights and interests of Taiwanese investors will be
protected by the law, no matter what happens, he added.
</P>
<P>
"We will continute to push forward the political negotiations
between the two sides of the Twaiwan Straits and anything can be
discussed under the principle of one China," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He also called for early opening of direct postal,
transport, and business links across the Taiwan Straits, saying
that it would save time and cost and have no ill effect.  
</P>
</TEXT>
