<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Bi Wenjing won the women's
uneven bars title at the Sagit Cup gymnastics competition, the
qualifying event in the World Cup series in Vancouver Saturday
night.
</P>
<P>
Her teammate Kui Yuanyuan also bagged home a gold medal in the
balance beam where Bi Wenjing finished second and Liu Xuan awarded
China another silver medal in the uneven bars.
</P>
