<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Music Copyright Auctioned Off in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The copyright to the music score
"Happiness", a popular Chinese melody, went for 580,000 yuan
(70,000 US dollars) at auction here today.
</P>
<P>
The music was written by Liu Mingyuan, a Chinese musician, in
1958. The tune has been used thousands of times over the past 40
years for holiday programs, ballroom parties, or various
celebration activities because of the excitement and enjoyment
that it causes.
</P>
<P>
The melody was created out of a local song from Shanxi
Province, and became popular in China from its very first
performance.
</P>
<P>
Also auctioned off were several valuable Erhus, the
two-stringed Chinese instrument that Liu Mingyuan used.
</P>
<P>
Wu Lianzhong, of the Beijing Auction Company, the auctioneers,
says that the proceeds from the auction will be given to a
foundation in Liu's name that promotes the use of traditional
Chinese music.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
