<HEADLINE> Portuguese Prime Minister Visiting Southwest China Municipality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Portuguese Prime Minister
Antonio Guterres arrived at the Municipality of Chongqing in
southwestern China today at the head of a 130-member delegation
for a five-day official visit.
</P>
<P>
He attended a signing ceremony for two bridges to be built and
operated by Chongqing, Portugal and Macao, and a Sino-Portuguese
economic and trade symposium. Work on the bridges will begin at
the end of this year. When they are completed in three years, they
will link different parts of the city.
</P>
<P>
Guterres noted that Chongqing is a development center for
southwest China and has been attracting more foreign
investors. The agreement signed today signals the beginning of
Portuguese cooperation with this part of China, he told those
present at the symposium.
</P>
<P>
Portugal intends to expand cooperation with China in industry,
service, and science and technology, and will try to serve as a
bridge between China and the European Union, he said.
</P>
<P>
Guterres and his party were honored at a dinner tonight given
by Zhang Delin, secretary of the Chongqing Municipal Committee of
the Chinese Communist Party. They will travel on to Shanghai and
Suzhou, then to Beijing on Tuesday. 
</P>
