following a botched attempt to assassinate a Hamas official,
Khaled Meshaal, in Amman, Jordan, enjoys high prestige among
Palestinians and is revered by Islamists throughout the Arab
world.
</P>
<P>
According to Iqbal Jhazbay, the director of University of
South Africa's Centre for Arabic and Islamic Studies, Omar and
Moosa met Yassin on April 7, in a royal guest house in Mina, a
town just outside Mecca. Jhazbay acted as interpreter at the
meeting,
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Yassin was well-briefed on South African
President Nelson Mandela's recent press conference with American
President Bill Clinton, in which Mandela defended South Africa's
ties with countries such as Libya and Iran.
</P>
<P>
Yassin expressed appreciation for Mandela's support for the
Palestinian cause, Jhazbay said.
</P>
<P>
The Sunday Independent quoted unidentified government
officials as saying that the half-hour meeting is of particular
significance because it suggests South Africa could play a role
in creating trust between Palestinians and Israelis. 
