<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Currency Further Depreciates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian currency Birr has
weakened to nearly 7 Birr against the US Dollar, which is the
lowest level since the currency was devalued in October, 1992.
</P>
<P>
The National Bank of Ethiopia announced Saturday that the
official exchange rate for Birr will be 6.997 Birr to one US
Dollar on April 20-26, 1998, compared to 6.988 Birr the previous
week.
</P>
<P>
On the foreign exchange auction held Saturday, the highest bid
rate was 7.115 Birr whereas the lowest bid rate was 6.921 for one
US Dollar, said the bank. The total amount of foreign exchange
made available at the auction amounted to 17 million Dollars and
bidders who offered rates of 6.997 and above for one US Dollar
won the full amount they tendered for, it added.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia introduced foreign exchange auction system in May,
1993. The auction is held weekly at the National Bank of
Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Commercial Bank of Ethiopia announced Saturday
that the buying price for US Dollar is 6.95 Birr while selling
price for the dollar is 7.1469. 
</P>
</TEXT>
