<HEADLINE> China Breaks Foreign Domination of Mobile Telecoms Equipment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- China has recently connected its
first home-made digital mobile telecommunications equipment with
the local network in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Ministry of Information Industry officials say China now has
managed to halt the foreign domination of its mobile
telecommunications equipment business and the achievement means
that China is one of the few countries capable of producing this
equipment.
</P>
<P>
The officials say the country will use both Chinese-made and
imported equipment to expand the telecommunications network with a
very flexible mix.
</P>
<P>
The GSM1800 digital mobile telecommunications system was
developed by the No.1 Research Institute of the ministry's
Telecommunications Science and Technology Institute and will be
used to improve the increasingly crowded GSM900 system that is
widely used in China at present.
</P>
<P>
The state-of-the-art equipment marks a major step forward in
China's move to commercialize its scientific and technological
achievements. Until last year, almost all the equipment was
imported or produced by Sino-foreign joint ventures.
</P>
<P>
The new Chinese-mde equipment did well during tests in Shanghai.
</P>
