<HEADLINE> Initial Success in Shipping Across Taiwan Straits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Direct shipping across the Taiwan
Straits has reached a higher stage of development after trials in
the past year, according to Fujian Province port authorities.
</P>
<P>
On April 19, 1997, a ship belonging to the Xiamen Steamship
Company went from Xiamen of Fujian to Taiwan's Kaohsiung, ending a
48-year lull in direct shipping between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
After going through a money-lossing period, regular direct
container shipping service has entered a stage of healthy
development, one Fujian port official said.
</P>
<P>
Nine container ships from nine shipping companies are now
operating across the Taiwan Straits and they had, by March 31,
made 1,286 round trips carrying 165,197 TEUs (twenty-foot
equivalent unit containers).
</P>
<P>
With a steady increase in business, the companies have managed
to turn losses into profits, the official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
