<HEADLINE> Last Respects to Chinese Artist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Party and government leaders
along with people from all walks of life came to pay their last
respects today to Xin Fengxia, a renowned Chinese artist, at the
Babaoshan revolutionary cemetery here.
</P>
<P>
The well-known performer of Pingju, a local opera of north
and northeast China, as well as painter and writer, died
suddenly of a cerebral haemorrhage on April 12 at the age of 71.
</P>
<P>
During her career as a performing artist, Xin performed in many
Pingju masterpieces and became famous across China.
</P>
<P>
She was also politically active and was elected a member of the
Sixth, Seventh and Eighth National Committees of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference.
</P>
<P>
Although she had been confined to a wheelchair since 1975
because of illness, her love of art and of the people never
dwindled and she continued to write, producing literary pieces
with over four million characters during her last years.
</P>
</TEXT>
