<HEADLINE> Shanghai Improves Vegetarian Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 19 (Xinhua) -- An increasing number of Shanghai
residents have gained an appreciation of vegetarian diets in
recent years, according to He Yizhao, deputy director of the
Shanghai Hotel Association.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is currently home to more than 2.3 million elderly
residents aged 60 and over, or 18.2 percent of the municipality's
population. The said residents also account for the majority of
vegetarians in the city, according to He.
</P>
<P>
A recent medical survey indicates an increasing number of liver
problems resulting from the changing diets of Shanghainese.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has a population of over 13 million, but a mere
10 vegetarian restaurants.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai should tap its vast potential to improve the
vegetarian market, according to He. 
