<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Four-time world 500cc
champion Australian Mick Doohan rode his Honda to win the 500cc
race in the Malaysian Grand Prix in Pasir Gudang, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Doohan was initially behind rival Max Biaggi from Italy but
took over the lead after the 21st round of the 30-lap championship
and never looked back.
</P>
<P>
Spain's Carlos Checa captured the second place while Biaggi
finished the third.
</P>
<P>
Doohan, who finished the race in 45 minutes and 15.533 seconds,
also held the record for the fastest lap of the race at 1:29.636
on lap three, established as the track's lap record in the 500cc
class.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Japanese riders Noboru Ueda and Tetsuya Harada
brought home the 125cc and 250cc titles respectively after both
benefitted from a last-corner crash on the final laps by their
opponents.
</P>
<P>
The next Grand Prix race will take place on May 3 at the Jerez
circuit in Spain. 
