<HEADLINE> Hongkong Telecom IMS to Offer Better Service to Internet Users </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The Hongkong Telecom IMS, the
largest Internet service provider (ISP) in Hong Kong, announced on
Sunday a series of measures to upgrade and reinforce its
technology, equipment and customer service.
</P>
<P>
One day after the second anniversary of the launching of the
Netvigator, Internet on-line service of the Hongkong Telecom IMS,
Managing Director William Lo said that the company will be the
first in Hong Kong to invest in one of the most powerful and
reliable email systems on the market, a commercial product adopted
by some of the largest ISPs and on-line services in the world.
</P>
<P>
"Though costly, the software migration underway will allow
Netvigator to offer world-class email service capable of
supporting long-term customer growth, with outstanding performance
and stability, as well as features such as anti-spamming," Lo
said.
</P>
<P>
Since early this month, three 56.6K modem pools have been put
into operation, which will help subscribers obtain easy
connections, Lo said.
</P>
<P>
Lo continued to say that Netvigator subscribers will enjoy free
usage from 9:00 AM to 5:00 PM everyday except Sundays, plus 50
hours per month of free usage during other time slots, which is in
effect a price reduction. The company will introduce more English
content to its site, Lo said.
</P>
<P>
The total access customers to the Netvigator rose from 100,000
to 245,000 from April 18, 1997 to 1998, which represents an
increase of 145 percent over the period from April 18, 1996 to
1997 and the Hongkong Telecom IMS occupied 44 percent of the
Internet market share in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Hongkong Telecom IMS was elected 1997 Best ISP in Hong Kong and
the netvigator.com was elected the 1997 Best Web site in Hong Kong
by the PC World, a world known computer magazine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
