Coming along with him are dozens of businessmen and six cabinet
ministers including Foreign Minister Jaime Gama, Economic Affairs
Minister Pina Moura, and Science and Technology Minister Mariano
Gago.
</P>
<P>
Guterres said that his visit to Macao and China's inland areas
was meant to "create an atmosphere of confidence and
understanding," apart from "stimulating Portuguese investment in
China."
</P>
<P>
During his visit to China's inland areas, he said he will
discuss the handover ceremony and other matters with Chinese
leaders. The handover will take place at midnight December 19,
1999. 
</P>
