<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Jayasinghe Insists on her Innocence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Susanthika Jayasinghe, the first
Sri Lankan runner to win a silver medal from the World Athletics
Championships, denied taking any banned substances when she
appeared before an inquiry panel here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Jayasinghe who failed an IAAF random drug test in March, was
suspended on April 10 after a second urine sample tested positive
for the steroid nandrolone, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Jayasinghe, runner-up in the women's 200 meters at the World
Championships last year in Athens, insisted in the hearing that
the bottles have not been sealed properly when being transmitted
from Colombo to Australia for drug testing.
</P>
<P>
However, the Australian laboratory said the bottles were packed
according to procedures. 
</P>
