<HEADLINE> One Israeli Settler Killed in West Bank Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 19 (Xinhua) -- One Israeli settler was shot
dead and another wounded Sunday in a violent clash near the West
Bank city Hebron due to a land dispute, Israeli Army said.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by Israeli Army Spokesman's Office said
a group of Palestinians ambushed several settlers in the hills
in Maom near Hebron. One of the Palestinians took over a gun
from the settlers and opened fire at them.
</P>
<P>
One settler was shot dead and another wounded in the shooting,
the statement added. The wounded was evacuated to hospital by a
military helicopter.
</P>
<P>
A large number of security forces were dispatched to the area
to conduct investigation into the incident and Army Central
Command head Uzi Dayan also visited the site.
</P>
<P>
The incident renewed the tension in the area near the
flashpoint town of Hebron. In the past month, widespread violent
clashes were sparked by a incident in which Israeli soldiers at a
checkpoint near Hebron shot dead three Palestinians on their way
home from working in Israel.
</P>
<P>
The latest incident also cast cloud on the visit Sunday here by
British Prime Minister Tony Blair, who is planning to create
favorable conditions for advancing the stalled Israeli-Palestinian
peace process by helping rebuild trust between Israelis and
Palestinians destroyed by repeated violence. 
</P>
