<HEADLINE> Haikou Attracts Increasing Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Haikou, capital of Hainan, China's
southernmost island province, has used foreign investment
totalling 4.1 billion US dollars over the past ten years.
</P>
<P>
The total included direct foreign investment of 2.86 billion
US dollars and foreign loans of 1.24 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Haikou's foreign-funded enterprises recorded total sales of
16.5 billion yuan (1.99 billion US dollars) over the past decade
of the establishment of the province, with exports standing at 380
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that foreign funds amounted to 510 million US
dollars of the city's fixed assets between 1996 and 1997, or 34.2
percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Foreign-funded enterprises exported products valued at 67.13
million US dollars during 1997, with the figure accounting for
33.8 percent of their total industrial sales revenue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
