<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hunan Establishes China's Most Extensive Classroom Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hunan Province
is in the process of establishing the "Network University", the
nation's most extensive classroom network system.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the network has been completed, with the
total project scheduled for completion at a cost of 50 million
yuan (6.02 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
People with access to a computer will have the ability to
receive wide-ranging instructional programs carried by the network.
</P>
<P>
The network currently links the Hunan capital of Changsha with
a number of provincial cities such as Zhuzhou, Xiangtan, Yiyang,
and Huaihua.
</P>
<P>
The Hunan University and the Hunan Teachers' University will
offer teaching courses on the network and have jointly enrolled
more than 2,000 students who will conduct self-studying via the
network. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
