<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-19 07:58 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait to Map out National Economic Strategy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti business community
leaders and government officials are to work out a coordinated
economic strategy for the Gulf state.
</P>
<P>
Abdul Wahab Al-Wassan, a board member of the Kuwait Chamber of
Commerce and Industry, was quoted by English daily Arab Times
Sunday as saying that a conference entitled "The role of the
Private Sector in Correcting the Economic Course" will be held on
April 20 to 21.
</P>
<P>
He said at the meeting the government will be represented by
five ministers, six parliamentary members, the Chairman of
Parliament's Financial and Economic Committee, the Chairman of
Parliament's Legislative Committee and the Governor of the Central
Bank.
</P>
<P>
The business community will be represented by the Kuwait
Chamber of Commerce and Industry, as well as a number of
independent specialists and experts.
</P>
<P>
Al-Wassan said the meeting will provide an opportunity for
Kuwait to address the incoherence surrounding its economic
strategy.
</P>
<P>
He said the meeting aims at helping the government in deciding
what strategies and plans to implement. Kuwait business community
believes that the Gulf state which depends mainly on oil for its
economy lacks a coherent economic strategy. Al-Wassan said "each
ministry has its own strategy, but there is no coordination."
</P>
<P>
The conference will be held at a time when Kuwait has adopted a
budget with the highest deficit since 1991, Kuwait's employment
policy is still under discussion and the implementation of a
privatization law has been pending for years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
