<HEADLINE> Chinese Local Government Delegation Leaves for U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- A group of China's local
government leaders left here today on a visit to the United States
at the invitation of the U.S. National Association of Counties.
</P>
<P>
The delegation was organized by the Chinese People's
Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries and is headed by
Sun Guizhang, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
Shanghai Municipal People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
The group will visit Hennepin County in the state of Minnesota,
King County in the state of Washington, Fairfax County in
Virginia, Howard County in Maryland, and several other cities.
</P>
<P>
Sun told Xinhua that the delegation is to visit the United
States at a time when Sino-U.S. relations have been developing in
a sound manner.
</P>
<P>
He noted the successful visit by President Jiang Zemin to the
United States last year and the forthcoming visit to China by
President Bill Clinton. He said that the delegation's visit will
help enhance mutual understandings between local government
leaders of the two countries and promote cooperation between the
two sides.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. National Association of Counties was established in
1935 and is the only national representative of county
governments. It has more than 3,000 member counties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
