<HEADLINE> Police Seize 1,600 Kilograms of Cocaine in Nicaragua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Nicaraguan antidrug police Friday
seized at least 1,600 kilograms of cocaine on a beach on the
Pacific coast 100 kilometers south of the capital.
</P>
<P>
Police caught four Colombians, one Guatemalan and one
Nicaraguan, who were allegedly involved in the case, newspapers
here reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Police also captured a Cigarreta-type speedboat, a Toyota land
cruiser pickup truck, and a large number of autoparts and arms,
including handguns, and M-16 and AK-47 rifles.
</P>
<P>
Mechanical failure of the speedboat since April 15 forced the
drug traffickers to unload the cocaine, packed in 73 bags, and
buried it in the beach near the Tola municipality in the Province
of Rivas, police sources said.
</P>
<P>
Police authorities speculate that the cocaine was probably from
Colombia and bound for the United States.
</P>
<P>
Rivas police chief Ernesto Zamora said police would continue
investigating the possible transit routes of drug traffickers.
</P>
<P>
In Penas Blancas of the Province of Rivas last February, police
confiscated a tank truck with more than 500 kilograms of cocaine.
</P>
