<HEADLINE> China Works to Restore Yellow River Shipping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, April 19 (Xinhua) -- China is working to restore
shipping in the upper reaches of the Yellow River in order to
alleviate the transportation bottleneck in the capital city of
Gansu Province.
</P>
<P>
Northwest China's Gansu Province plans to dredge 38.4 km of
river channel near Lanzhou, the provincial capital, by October
next year. Plans also call for the construction of 14 docks, and
telecommunications and navigation systems in the section.
</P>
<P>
Dredging operations have already been completed on
approximately one-third of the section.
</P>
<P>
Once the 45 million yuan operations are completed, the section
will have an annual transportation capacity of 300,000 passengers
and 500,000 tons of cargo. Related operations will also promote
the development of the service industry and greatly enhance
environmental protection in Lanzhou City. 
</P>
