<HEADLINE> Seles, Davenport Give U.S. 2-0 Lead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Monica Seles and Lindsay
Davenport on Saturday gave the United States a 2-0 first round
lead in its Fed Cup tennis match against the Netherlands in Kiawah
Island, South Carolina.
</P>
<P>
Seles beat 53rd-ranked Miriam Oremans 6-1, 6-2 in less than an
hour.
</P>
<P>
Davenport started slowly against 200th-ranked Amanda Hopmans
before winning eight of the last nine games for a 6-4, 6-1 win in
80 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The winner of this tie will move into the semi-finals against
either Germany or Spain, which split their two singles matches
Saturday in Saarbrucken, Germany. 
</P>
