<HEADLINE> Belgium, France One Win Each in Fed Cup Tie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Hosts Belgium came from match
down to draw visitors France to one-all in their Federation Cup
World Group One tie on Saturday in the Belgian city of Gent.
</P>
<P>
Sabine Appelmans was the first up for the hosts but could not
hold on to Sandrine Testud's speed and force, only to drop the
first of the opening singles 6-3, 6-2 in a little over one hour.
</P>
<P>
Dominique Monami van Roost almost followed suit in losing the
second of the day's match after she fought 50 minutes before
allowing Sarah Pitkowski to take the first set 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Van Roost, ranked 14th on the WTA tour, recollected her
confidence in front of a supporting home crowd and built up her
play via placement shots in the ensuing set which she took 6-4 in
43 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The tie-breaking third turned out too much for fatigued
Pitkowski who was ranked 44th on the WTA tour and the Frenchwoman
could not find the deep lobs that she had used to move van Roost
from side to side along the baseline in previous sets.
</P>
<P>
The Belgian player took the set 6-2 and the match in 29 minutes
to put the hosts back on equal footing with the French side for
Sunday's reverse singles.
</P>
<P>
The winner of the Belgian-French tie will meet the winner of
the Czech-Swiss tie in mid July. 
</P>
