<HEADLINE> Central China Province to Spend 23 Billion Yuan on Highways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- In the coming three years ending
2000, spending on highway construction in central China's Hunan
Province will reach 23 billion yuan, more than three times the
figure during the 1991-1995 period.
</P>
<P>
Of that amount, 17 billion yuan will come from overseas
financial institutions and be raised by issuing stocks, and the
remaining six billion yuan will come from transferring highway
managerial rights.
</P>
<P>
By 2000, local highways will have been extended from the
current 59,761 kilometers to 61,500 kilometers, including 455
kilometers of expressways, a big increase from the present 45
kilometers. 
</P>
