<HEADLINE> WBO Champion Hide Beats American in 52 seconds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Herbie Hide of Britain spent less
than a minute to beat over-matched American heavyweight Damon Reed
to score a first-round knockout victory in his second defense of
the WBO championship In Manchester, England on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Hide floored Reed only 20 seconds into the fight with a right
followed by by a left hook.
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old American went down in the corner and was up at
eight.
</P>
<P>
Hide quickly followed up with big right hands that had Reed
covering up on the ropes but it was a one-sided contest and
referee Rudy Battle moved in to halt the fight after only 52
seconds.
</P>
<P>
Reed was helped back to his corner. His record slipped to
22-2-1 while Hide improved to 30-1-0. 
